The paper deals with the problem of secret communication over a multiple-access channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of a common message and the study of the Gaussian version of the problem suggest that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and networking (cs.NI). Finally, the focus on secrecy and privacy aligns with the sub-category of security and privacy (cs.SI).
